<subSubSection id="EBEABDD9FF86FFFA39D308EC431DBF87" pageId="8" pageNumber="235" type="description">
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FF86FFFA39D308EC431DBF87" blockId="8.[136,1452,986,1661]" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis id="91843240FF86FFFA39D308EC47FDB8DB" bold="true" box="[136,211,986,1012]" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">Shrub</emphasis>
<quantity id="640843B7FF86FFFA398608EC467EB8DA" box="[221,336,986,1013]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="235" unit="cm" value="55.0" valueMax="70.0" valueMin="40.0">40–70 cm</quantity>
tall. 
<emphasis id="91843240FF86FFFA38CB08EC46CCB8DB" bold="true" box="[400,482,986,1012]" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">Leaves</emphasis>
with 5–9 pairs of pinnae; 5–11 pairs of leaflets; rachis nectaries 1–2, verruciform; blade usually chartaceous, margin sparsely puberule at least near the base and at the apex, leaflets 1.5–2.9(–3.5) × 1.2–2(–2.5) cm, discolor to rarely subconcolor, upper surface glabrous, lower surface sparsely puberule with a denser indumentum along the midrib, near the base and the apex, unilateral tuft of trichomes on the lower surface present. 
<emphasis id="91843240FF86FFFA39D30F5C461FBFAB" bold="true" box="[136,305,1130,1156]" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">Inflorescences</emphasis>
of simple thyrsi; cymulae of usually solitary spikes, rarely geminate, vinaceous. 
<emphasis id="91843240FF86FFFA3D8D0F5C421BBFAB" bold="true" box="[1238,1333,1130,1156]" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">Flowers</emphasis>
diclinous, vinaceous. 
<emphasis id="91843240FF86FFFA385D0FB8466ABF87" bold="true" box="[262,324,1166,1192]" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">Fruit</emphasis>
a follicule, straight, flat-compressed, valves dark-brown (
<figureCitation id="3BCBF2D7FF86FFFA3A960FB8430BBF87" box="[973,1061,1166,1192]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="9.[136,229,1992,2014]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,190,1968]" captionTargetId="figure-17@9.[189,1398,190,1968]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 2. Subshrub species of Stryphnodendron. A. Stryphnodendron heringeri Occhioni f.; B. Stryphnodendron barbatulum Rizzini &amp; Heringer; C. Stryphnodendron platyspicum Rizzini &amp; Heringer; D. &amp; E. Stryphnodendron cristalinae Heringer, the woody underground root-like system in detail." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520284/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBEABDD9FF86FFFA39E60F844208BE3A" pageId="8" pageNumber="235" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FF86FFFA39E60F844208BE3A" blockId="8.[136,1452,986,1661]" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis id="91843240FF86FFFA39E60F84461ABFE3" bold="true" box="[189,308,1202,1228]" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">Remarks:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FF86FFFA380B0F8546DCBFE3" authorityName="Rizzini &amp; Heringer" authorityYear="1987" box="[336,498,1202,1229]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="barbatulum">
<emphasis id="91843240FF86FFFA380B0F8546DCBFE3" box="[336,498,1202,1229]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">S. barbatulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FF86FFFA3B6B0F8545FBBFE3" authorityName="Heringer &amp; Rizzini (Rizzini &amp; Heringer" authorityYear="1987" box="[560,725,1202,1229]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sallesianum">
<emphasis id="91843240FF86FFFA3B6B0F8545FBBFE3" box="[560,725,1202,1229]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">S. sallesianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were originally treated as distinct taxa based only in the 
<typeStatus id="7C4B50F0FF86FFFA3C200F854285BFE2" box="[1403,1451,1203,1229]" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">type</typeStatus>
collection, but the analysis of new specimens revealed many intermediary characteristics mainly in respect to pinnae number and size, and with identical follicle fruits. Based on this, 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FF86FFFA3A3A0FCD432DBE3B" authorityName="Heringer &amp; Rizzini (Rizzini &amp; Heringer" authorityYear="1987" box="[865,1027,1274,1301]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sallesianum">
<emphasis id="91843240FF86FFFA3A3A0FCD432DBE3B" box="[865,1027,1274,1301]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">S. sallesianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is considered a synonym.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBEABDD9FF86FFFA39E60E284321BD1B" pageId="8" pageNumber="235" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FF86FFFA39E60E2845EDBE72" blockId="8.[136,1452,986,1661]" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis id="91843240FF86FFFA39E60E2846C9BE17" bold="true" box="[189,487,1310,1336]" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
—This species is only known from the 
<typeStatus id="7C4B50F0FF86FFFA3AC30E2944E6BE16" box="[920,968,1311,1337]" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">type</typeStatus>
locality, region of Granja do Torto, Brasília (
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF86FFFA39D40E74466BBE72" box="[143,325,1346,1373]" country="Brazil" name="Distrito Federal" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">Federal District</collectingRegion>
), where it occurs in cerrado areas.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FF86FFFA39E60E504321BD1B" blockId="8.[136,1452,986,1661]" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis id="91843240FF86FFFA39E60E504649BEAF" bold="true" box="[189,359,1382,1408]" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">Conservation:</emphasis>
—Critically Endangered (CR B2ab(ii,iii)) [AOO= 
<quantity id="640843B7FF86FFFA3ACD0E50432CBEAF" box="[918,1026,1382,1408]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="235" unit="km" value="4.0">4.000 km</quantity>
<superScript id="5485431AFF86FFFA3D590E504324BE5B" attach="left" box="[1026,1034,1382,1396]" fontSize="6" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">2</superScript>
, EOO not measurable]. Although the reduced size of the individuals makes it difficult to visually estimate the size of the populations, the species occurs in an area that has received considerable collecting efforts in the last decades. However, there are no recent collections of this taxon and recent visits to the region revealed a very small fragment of remaining native vegetation, though not occupied by residences, but taken by ruderal plants. The area is indisputably under extreme anthropogenic pressure, and thus 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FF86FFFA39B60D2C4517BD1B" authorityName="Rizzini &amp; Heringer" authorityYear="1987" box="[237,569,1562,1588]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="235" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="barbatulum">
<emphasis id="91843240FF86FFFA39B60D2C4517BD1B" box="[237,569,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">Stryphnodendron barbatulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here considered Critically Endangered.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBEABDD9FF86FFFA39E60D084697BD53" pageId="8" pageNumber="235" type="description">
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FF86FFFA39E60D084697BD53" blockId="8.[136,1452,986,1661]" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis id="91843240FF86FFFA39E60D08466DBD77" bold="true" box="[189,323,1598,1624]" pageId="8" pageNumber="235">Phenology:</emphasis>
—Flowering samples of this species were collected in September and November, fruiting samples were collected in February.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
